question:
i have a div changing background color from transparent to rgb(160, 69, 69). i want the transition to be color translation from left then complete to the rigth. here is the css code ia have: 
.hover-item {
 height: 2px!important;
 background-color: transparent!important;
}

.nav-item:hover .hover-item{
 background-color: rgb(160, 69, 69)!important;
 transition: all ease-in 1s;
}

answer:
You can use the `background-position` and `background-size` properties along with a background image to achieve this effect. Here's how you can modify your CSS:
```css
.hover-item {
    height: 2px;
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, rgb(160, 69, 69));
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: 0% 100%;
    background-position: left center;
    transition: background-size ease-in 1s;
}

.nav-item:hover .hover-item {
    background-size: 100% 100%;
}
```

This code uses a gradient that starts with `transparent` on the left and transitions to the desired color `rgb(160, 69, 69)` on the right. The `background-size` property is responsible for the width of the gradient, so when it's set to `100%`, the full effect is visible.

