In the code above, we've added an `offsetTop` property with a value of `-10` pixels to the `scrollIntoView` method. This will move the selected element 10 pixels down from the top of the scrolling div, effectively compensating for the extra scroll distance. You can adjust the value of `offsetTop` to fine-tune the scroll position as needed.

